Pre-installation Instructions
=============================

   This installation requires the pre-installation of the cmake tool,
a C++ compiler, and the libraries: zlib, libdatrie, libdivsufsort, sdsl, 
and MultiFast (Aho-Corasick automaton).

For Ubuntu Linux, make sure your are on-line, and install the above via

 $ ./pre-install.sh 

Basic Instructions
==================

   The shell command `make' should compile this example program. 

After compilation the binary `example' will be created in the working 
directory, e.g. you may call it from this directory via

 S ./example ./data/text0 ./data/pattern0 0

 $ ./example ./data/text1 ./data/pattern1 1

 $ ./example ./data/text2 ./data/pattern2 2
